NAME
     d.colors - Interactive program for changing category colors
     of a cell
     (Available through grass3 menu)

SYNOPSIS
     d.colors [cell_file]

DESCRIPTION
     The GRASS tool d.colors is used to change the colors
     associated with the categories of a cell Before running
     d.colors, the cell of interest should be displayed using
     Dcell.  If Dcolormode is set to "float" the colors on the
     display will change interactively.  Otherwise, if Dcolormode
     is "fixed", colors will not change as you run d.colors;
     however, you can save changed colors (which will then appear
     next time the is Note that some or drivers cannot
     interactively change color.

     The user can enter the name of the cell whose color table is
     to be changed on the command line (e.g., d.colors soils).
     If the cell name is not entered on the command line,
     d.colors will ask the user to enter the name of an existing
     cell The d.colors command menu is listed below. The command
     menu for d.colors is the same as the category and color
     changing portion of the display menu.  The d.colors commands
     are listed beneath the Category Pointer Movement, Color
     Modification, Replotting Screen, and Quitting sections
     below.  Commands are invoked by typing in the single-key
     response shown to the left below.  (Longer descriptions of
     these commands appear to the right.) Results from invoking
     these commands will be reflected in the Category and
     Category Number sections of the d.colors screen.  On the
     d.colors screen menu, commands appear in the right half of
     the screen, and the current status of categories appears in
     the left half of the screen.
