     Color table toggle - Different types of color tables are
     suitable for different The key t flips between the following
     color tables: red, green, blue color ramp; gray scale;
     smooth changing color wave; random colors; and the saved
     color table.

     Color table shift - The entire table is shifted up and down
     using the + and - keys.

     Quitting the d.colors program - Pressing the Q key will
     cause you to quit the d.colors program.  If colors have been
     modified but not saved, d.colors will ask: Colors changed
     but not saved
     OK to quit?  The user should type in y if yes, or n if no,
     at this point.

